                        <support>
                           <p><material key="marmor">Marble</material> 
                              <objectType>sarcophagus</objectType>,  later used  with a different <objectType>sarcophagus lid</objectType>: 
                              <dimensions><height unit="metre">0.74 and 0.32</height> <width unit="metre">2.07</width> <depth unit="metre">0.83</depth></dimensions>. 
                              on the front a tabula originally framed by two Erotes and garlands, which were later carved away; two standing figures: at left Pan, at right probably Dionysos 
                              (with a small quadruped at his feet); on the short sides the original decoration was erased; in the pediments of the lid, what looks like a poorly 
                              executed agonistic crown. 
                              Remains of three inscriptions: <hi rend="bold">A</hi> and <hi rend="bold">B</hi> from the first use, <hi rend="bold">C</hi> from the re-use.</p>
                        </support>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           A <rs type="execution" ref="scalpro">Inscribed</rs>  on the lifting boss of the lid and B at the top of the chest (3 lines, erased) 
                           and on the tabula, mostly erased lines; C, inscribed later, is in two long lines on the lid.</layout>
